            <title>[CASSANDRA-5967] Allow local batchlog writes for CL.ANY</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5967</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We tell people that ANY means you can write if even a single node is reachable.  We should apply that to batchlog writes as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: we already allow local batchlog writes for any single-node datacenter; batchlog writes are synchronous, so cross-dc latency would be slow enough to be unusable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
